      "type": "text",
      "name": "intro_text",
      "value": "Small acts of kindness can have a big impact. This activity helps children to think about others and what they can do to bring joy to someone’s day.",
      "_translations": {
        "value": {
          "tz_sw": true
        }
      },
      "_nested_name": "intro_text"
    },
    {
      "name": "text_1",
      "value": "Together with your child, think of something special you could do for someone at home or in your community to put a smile on their face.\n1. **Choose a person.** Discuss with your child who you think might appreciate an act of kindness. \n2. **Discuss the options together.** For example: *“Mama has been feeling so tired taking care of baby sister and never gets time to make herself tea. What do you think we could do for her?” or “I see that xx next door struggles to care for her garden. What do you think we can do to help?”*\n3. **Support your child to contribute.** Help your child to choose what they can do. It doesn’t have to be big – all that matters is that they are part of the activity in some way.\n4. **Praise your child** for helping to bring joy to someone’s day. This will encourage them to do it again in future.",
      "_translations": {
        "value": {
          "tz_sw": true
        }
      },
      "type": "set_variable",
      "_nested_name": "text_1"
    },
    {
      "name": "text_2",
      "value": "* Your child’s involvement will vary with age, but even a three year old can add a scribble or drawing to a card, hand over a flower, or join in a song.  \n* Try not to force your child or punish them if they feel shy or don’t want to participate. Rather try again another time.",
      "_translations": {
        "value": {
          "tz_sw": true
        }
      },
      "type": "set_variable",
      "_nested_name": "text_2"
